President Obama released a statement praising Senator Byron Dorgan for his 30 years of service in the United States Congress and to the people of North Dakota. The President highlighted Dorgan's efforts in fighting for the energy future and supporting North Dakota's families during tough economic times. He also recognized Dorgan as a champion for family farmers and for his work to improve Indian health care services. President Obama expressed gratitude for Dorgan's service to the nation and extended best wishes to him and his family for the future.